description: Here's a look at the top stories making headlines on the "CBS Evening News with Norah O'Donnell."
title: "CBS Evening News" headlines for Friday, Oct. 18, 2024

description: The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration published its winter outlook for this coming December, January and February. Experts anticipate warmer-than-average temperatures for much of the country. CBS News Sacramento meteorologist Tracy Humphrey joins to discuss.
title: NOAA predicting warmer than average winter

description: A new report published by Stop AAPI Hate shows a recent rise in hate and discrimination against South Asian Americans. The nonprofit organization found that 75% of anti-Asian online threats in August were directed toward South Asians. Manjusha Kulkarni, co-founding partner of Stop AAPI Hate, joins CBS News to dig through the findings.
title: Report finds hate against South Asians in U.S. rising

description: Marine veteran Paul Whelan is speaking out for the first time since his release from Russian imprisonment. Whelan spoke with "Face the Nation" moderator Margaret Brennan about the toll of life in captivity. Ryan Fayhee, Whelan's lawyer, joins CBS News to discuss.
title: Paul Whelan's attorney reflects on effort to bring him home

description: A judge on Friday unsealed more than 1,800 pages of documents in the federal 2020 election interference case against former President Donald Trump. Much of the unsealed documents, including interview transcripts and court hearings, remain heavily redacted. CBS News congressional correspondent Scott MacFarlane has the details.
title: What we learned from newly unsealed evidence in Trump election case

description: White House national security communications adviser John Kirby said Friday that Hamas is in a "dramatically weakened position" following the killing of its leader Yahya Sinwar. His death has opened many questions about the future of the Israel-Hamas war and the possibility of a cease-fire and hostage release deal. CBS News foreign correspondent Ramy Inocencio has the latest.
title: Hamas "dramatically weakened" after Sinwar death, White House says

description: The Texas man will testify before the Committee on Criminal Jurisprudence of the Texas House of Representatives.
title: Robert Roberson expected to testify before legislative panel after execution stay

description: The frozen waffles, made by Treehouse Foods, were sold under store brands including Walmart's Great Value and Target's Good and Gather.
title: Frozen waffles sold at Walmart and other stores recalled over listeria

description: Navigating the insurance process after a natural disaster damages your home can be daunting. Here are some key tips.
title: What to know about filing an insurance claim after a hurricane

description: A fast-moving vegetation fire broke out Friday afternoon in the hills of Oakland, California, burning multiple homes before firefighters were able to stop forward progress hours after the incident began.
title: Fire burns hillside homes in Oakland amid day of high winds; residents evacuated

description: A rare copy of the U.S. Constitution forgotten inside a filing cabinet​ sold on Thursday for a $9 million hammer price, the auction house confirmed to CBS News.
title: A rare copy of the U.S. Constitution sells for $9 million at auction

description: A massive outage left millions of Cubans without power and prompted the government Friday to implement emergency measures to slash demand.
title: Massive blackout hits Cuba after major power plant fails

description: Donald Trump said he'd appoint a CEO who is 78, his own age. But chief executives of top companies who are his age or older are rare.
title: Trump says he'd hire a 78-year-old CEO. There aren't many of them.

description: Former President Donald Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris have their eyes set on Michigan, where both are focused on voters blue counties that could help better chances for either candidate in the general election. CBS News' Zak Hudak has more.
title: Harris, Trump campaigns trying to win over these valuable Michigan voters

description: Ofir Akunis, the Consul General of Israel in New York, says Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar was caught while he was trying to escape through the Philadelphi Corridor. Akunis joined CBS News with more details on the Israeli military operation that led to Sinwar's death.
title: Yahya Sinwar was trying to escape through Philadelphi Corridor, Israeli official says

description: NOAA has released its seasonal outlook for the winter months, which predicts the U.S. will slowly transition into a La Niña pattern.
title: Maps show NOAA's winter outlook

description: Richard Allen's trial is underway in Indiana. Allen is accused of killing two teenage girls in a case known as the Delphi murders. He pleaded not guilty to all charges. CBS News' Meg Oliver reports.
title: Opening statements in Delphi murder trial

description: Former President Donald Trump's lawyer sought a new nondisclosure agreement from adult film star Stormy Daniels, documents provided to CBS News by Daniels' attorney Clark Brewster show.
title: Trump wanted new Stormy Daniels NDA this year, documents show

description: New images released by South Korean officials appear to show North Korea's attempts to move troops over to Russia to aid in the war against Ukraine. CBS News senior national security correspondent Charlie D'Agata has more.
title: New images appear to show North Korea troops headed to Russia for Ukraine war

description: The Israel Defense Forces provided more details on the operation that led to the killing of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar in the Gaza Strip. Video of Sinwar's apparent last moments alive was also released. CBS News' Haley Ott has the latest.
title: New details of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar's last moments alive

description: A $75,000 HELOC has inexpensive monthly payments now, and they could become even cheaper in the months to come.
title: How much will a $75,000 HELOC cost per month now that rates are falling?

description: Death of top Hamas leader sparks renewed hope for ceasefire in Gaza; Why saving for retirement has become a challenge for the "sandwich generation."
title: Oct 18: CBS News 24/7, 1pm ET

description: With only weeks before the November 5 election, here's how top economists assess the health of the U.S. economy.
title: How is the economy really doing just weeks before the U.S. election?

description: Just weeks before the 2024 general election, Judge Tanya Chutkan unsealed evidence in the election interference case against former President Donald Trump after his lawyers requested a delay until after the race ends. CBS News' Scott MacFarlane has more.
title: Trump election interference case evidence unsealed after Jack Smith filing

description: The Texas Supreme Court ruled to stay Robert Roberson's execution after a last-attempt appeal by his lawyers and lawmakers was granted. CBS News' Nikki Battiste reports.
title: Behind the Texas court decision to stay Robert Roberson's execution

description: The judge presiding over Donald Trump's election interference case unsealed some evidence filed by special counsel Jack Smith in his case against the former president. CBS News' Scott MacFarlane has more.
title: New details unsealed in Trump election interference case

description: Former President Donald Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris are holding dueling events in Michigan as both candidates try to court enough voters to swing the battleground state for their 2024 campaigns. CBS News political reporters Olivia Rinaldi and Aaron Navarro have more.
title: Harris, Trump in Michigan to court key battleground voters

description: "If Mr. Trump returns, we will open multiple bottles of champagne," Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán said earlier this month.
title: 2 populist European leaders openly hope for a Trump election victory

description: Deputy Hamas leader Khalil al-Hayya has confirmed Yahya Sinwar's death and said the remaining Oct. 7, 2023, hostages will not be released until a cease-fire deal is reached and Israeli troops withdraw from Gaza. CBS News' Haley Ott has more from Tel Aviv, and CBS News' Willie James Inman has more on Biden's response to the developments in the Middle East.
title: Hamas says hostages won't be released without Israel cease-fire deal

description: Walmart's prefab house includes space for a bedroom, living room, bathroom, dining room and kitchen, but appliances are sold separately.
title: Walmart is selling a tiny house for less than $16,000

description: The price of gold has surpassed yet another price record. Here's why you shouldn't wait any longer to get invested.
title: Gold's price soars past a record $2,700: Why you should invest right now

description: Richard Allen, 52, is facing two counts of murder in the killings of Delphi, Indiana eighth graders Abigail Williams and Liberty German.
title: What to know about the Delphi murders as trial gets underway

description: An American Airlines 737 and a Cessna 182 came within about 350 feet of each other in mid-air near the airport in Austin, Texas.
title: FAA investigating mid-air close call in Austin, Texas

description: The worst rates of the infection known as  "walking pneumonia" or "white lung pneumonia" are in young children ages 2 to 4 years old.
title: Unusual surge of "walking pneumonia" reported in kids this year

description: President Biden spoke to reporters before departing Germany. Mr. Biden commented on the potential to move forward with cease-fires in Lebanon and Gaza after Israel's operation that killed Hamas' leader Yahya Sinwar. Mr. Biden also said he has a good understanding of Israel's plans and timing for a response to Iran's recent attack.
title: Biden on Israel's plans to respond to Iran attack, Middle East peace

description: The U.S. is calling the death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar an opportunity for the end of the Israel-Hamas war. CBS News senior national security correspondent Charlie D'Agata has more.
title: How Sinwar killing impacts efforts to end Israel-Hamas war

description: A judge has unsealed more evidence collected by special counsel Jack Smith in the federal 2020 election interference case against Donald Trump. CBS News legal contributor Caroline Polisi has the latest.
title: Evidence unsealed in federal 2020 election interference case against Trump

description: The pills seized had an estimated street value of $13.6 million, officials said.
title: 6 million pills seized, 47 arrested in major drug smuggling bust

description: Opening statements are getting underway Friday in Delphi, Indiana, for the murder trial of Richard Allen, the suspect in the 2017 killings of 13-year-old Abigail Williams and 14-year-old Liberty German. CBS News correspondent Meg Oliver has more.
title: Delphi murders trial gets underway in Indiana

description: The judge overseeing President Donald Trump's 2020 election interference case released more evidence collected by special counsel Jack Smith on Friday.
title: Judge unseals more evidence in Trump 2020 election case

description: Newly released video from the U.S. Coast Guard shows the rescue of 17-year-old Kahiau Kawai, a kayaker who spent nearly 12 hours lost amid stormy seas. A volunteer lifeguard was key to his safe return, officials said.
title: Video shows rescue of teen kayaker who was lost at sea nearly 12 hours

description: Kamala Harris held a rally in Wisconsin Thursday night where she mocked Donald Trump for his recent comments about IVF and said the former president has no idea what he's talking about on women's health care in America. CBS News campaign reporter Aaron Navarro has more.
title: Harris says Trump has no idea what he's talking about when it comes to women's health care

description: Former President Trump attended the Al Smith dinner in New York Thursday night, a traditional event on the campaign calendar that Kamala Harris chose not to attend, which Trump called disrespectful. CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi has more.
title: Breaking down Trump's comments at the Al Smith dinner

description: President Biden on Friday in Berlin addressed U.S. allies on Israel's killing of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, calling it a moment of justice and urging a path to peace. CBS News White House reporter Willie James Inman has more on Biden's comments and what to expect from the rest of his trip to Europe.
title: Biden calls killing of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar a moment of justice

description: Rwanda says it's gaining control of a Marburg outbreak, but U.S. authorities are taking no chances as another killer virus spreads fast.
title: U.S. boosts passenger screening as Marburg and mpox viruses spread

description: The bestselling novelist returns with a work of non-fiction, co-written by the founder of an organization advocating for the wrongfully-convicted, that details the painful stories of people convicted for crimes they did not commit.
title: Book excerpt: "Framed" by John Grisham and Jim McCloskey

description: U.S. officials are hoping Israel's killing of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar will lead to some kind of diplomatic settlement for the war in Gaza and the release of the hostages still held by Hamas. CBS News chief foreign affairs correspondent Margaret Brennan has more on that and her interview with Paul Whelan about his years-long imprisonment in Russia.
title: White House calls Hamas significantly weakened after Israel kills Yahya Sinwar

description: A new report by House Democrats accuses Trump of charging the Secret Service "exorbitant rates" when agents stayed at his hotel as the protective detail for Trump family members.
title: Trump overcharged Secret Service to stay at his D.C. hotel, report says

description: A day after an IDF operation killed Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, the Lebanese-based Hezbollah militant group has vowed to launch a new phase of fighting against Israel. CBS News reporter Haley Ott has more.
title: Hezbollah vowing to escalate fight against Israel after Hamas leader killed in Gaza

description: IDF international spokesman Major Doron Spielman joined CBS News to talk about Thursday's operation that killed Hamas chief Yahya Sinwar and where Israel's war with Hamas goes from here.
title: IDF spokesman on killing of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, state of Israel-Hamas war

description: A $30,000 debt balance can be debilitating for your finances. Here's how much a forgiveness plan can reduce it by.
title: Stuck with $30,000 in credit card debt? Here's how much a forgiveness plan can cover.

description: Jay Cutler was arrested for a DUI, gun possession and other charges in Franklin, Tennessee on Thursday evening, an official confirmed to CBS News.
title: Ex-NFL quarterback Jay Cutler arrested for DUI and gun possession

description:
Bill Whitaker reports on the bombing of the Cap Arcona, a little-known human tragedy in the closing days of World War II. Once a luxurious German ocean liner, the Cap Arcona was commandeered by
 the Nazis and turned into a floating concentration camp. 60 Minutes, Sunday.
title: The Cap Arcona | Sunday on 60 Minutes

description: The latest CBS News polling in Arizona shows former President Donald Trump with a slim lead within the margin of error. However, in the closely watched Senate race, Trump ally Kari Lake is trailing.
title: Trump leads in Arizona, but Kari Lake struggles in Senate race, CBS News poll shows

description: Opening statements are set for today in the trial of Richard Allen, who is charged with the 2017 murders of 13-year-old Abby Williams and 14-year-old Libby German. Allen has pleaded not guilty to the charges.
title: Opening statements begin today in Delphi trial for man accused of killing two teenage girls

description: The animals contracted melioidosis, possibly after some digging work near their cages, that later caused them to develop sepsis, officials said.
title: Hong Kong zoo officials reveal what killed 9 monkeys

description: We're learning about Liam Payne's final moments before the former One Direction singer plunged from a hotel balcony on Wednesday. Fans around the world have set up memorials for him. The other members of One Direction say they are "completely devastated."
title: Liam Payne's final moments revealed before tragic hotel balcony fall

description: 81-year-old tennis player Gabe Temesvari and Todd Boynton met by chance on the court and formed a close friendship, despite their 25-year age difference. The two now play pickleball together.
title: Unlikely friendship blossoms on the pickleball court between two men 25 years apart

description: Following the death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, President Biden called it an "opportunity for peace." Margaret Brennan joins us to explore how this development could affect the ongoing fighting in Gaza.
title: How Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar's death will impact the Israel-Hamas war

description: In today's tough housing market, homebuyers face high mortgage rates—but it's not the first time. A CBS News report from 1979 shows a young family in Chicago struggling with even steeper rates of 11%. Here's a look back at how history is repeating itself.
title: "Mornings Memory": Buying a home in 2024 echoes the challenges of 1979

description: A 2019 survey found that 68% of women between ages 35 and 54 are nervous about dating again post-divorce. Professional matchmaker Maria Avgitidis shares her expert tips on finding love after divorce.
title: Navigating the dating scene after divorce

description: As the race in Michigan tightens, former President Donald Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris delivered sharp critiques of each other, with Trump making pointed comments at a charity dinner and Harris condemning his remarks about Jan. 6.
title: Trump and Harris trade sharp attacks as 2024 presidential race heats up

description: Gordon Lubold from The Wall Street Journal joins "CBS Mornings Plus" to discuss the rise in drone activity over restricted U.S. military airspaces.
title: Inside growing drone threat the U.S. faces with multiple breaches of restricted airspace

description: Colt Gray, the 14-year-old suspect in a Georgia school shooting, now faces a potential life sentence. His father, Colin Gray, faces numerous charges for allegedly ignoring warning signs that could have prevented the tragedy.
title: New charges filed against Georgia school shooting suspect and his father

description: A lawyer for former President Donald Trump asked Stormy Daniels to promise not to speak about her "interactions" with Trump or question "his suitability as a candidate for president," documents show.
title: Trump sought new NDA from Stormy Daniels this year, documents show

description: The Texas Supreme Court has halted the execution of Robert Roberson, who was convicted of killing his daughter based on a controversial diagnosis of "shaken baby syndrome." The case has drawn widespread attention due to disputed medical evidence.
title: Texas Supreme Court blocks execution of man convicted in disputed "shaken baby syndrome" case

description: A look at the features for this week's broadcast of the Emmy-winning program, hosted by Jane Pauley.
title: This week on "Sunday Morning" (October 20)

description: When volunteer lifeguard Noland Keaulana heard that 17-year-old Kahiau Kawai was missing at sea, he leapt into action.
title: Volunteer lifeguard saves teen kayaker lost at sea for 12 hours

description: President Biden said it's important for Ukraine's Western allies to "sustain our resolve" in supporting the country as he held meetings Friday with European partners.
title: Biden meets with European allies in Berlin, says West must keep aiding Ukraine

description: Since its debut in 2020, "Kindness 101" has captured millions of hearts. Now, with a new curriculum created in partnership with Drake University, Steve Hartman and his kids are visiting classrooms to highlight students who embody kindness and character.
title: "Kindness 101" brings lessons of kindness to classrooms nationwide

description: Owen Han, known as the "Sandwich King" on TikTok, has captivated fans with his delicious sandwich creations, racking up hundreds of millions of views. Now, he's sharing his recipes in a new cookbook, "Stacked: The Art of the Perfect Sandwich."
title: "The Dish": TikTok's "Sandwich King" Owen Han shares secret to crafting the perfect sandwich

description: As "Blue Bloods" enters its final stretch of new episodes, the Reagan family continues to capture audiences. Star Tom Selleck and the cast discuss the show's lasting impact and the iconic family dinner scenes that have become a fan favorite.
title: "Blue Bloods" actors on show's success, their close-knit on-screen family

description: In April 2018, prosecutors say a "throuple" walked into a Florida motel room but only a couple walked out. "48 Hours" correspondent Peter Van Sant shares how investigators connected back-to-back crime scenes to track down the suspects.
title: Florida investigators unravel murder victim's "throuple" past in search of clues

description: Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, who has been a prime target for Israel, was killed in Gaza. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu called it "the beginning of the end," but stated that Israel's military mission is not yet complete.
title: Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar killed: What it means for the conflict in Gaza

description: The IDF confirmed that Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar has been killed. Meanwhile, CBS News' Margaret Brennan sits down with Paul Whelan for his first interview since being freed from a Russian prison. All that and all that matters in today's Eye Opener.
title: Eye Opener: Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar killed in Gaza

description: Taylor Swift is returning to the stage Thursday night in Miami for the final leg of her Eras Tour after a nearly two-month hiatus. CBS News Miami reporter Morgan Rynor has more.
title: Taylor Swift's Eras Tour to "begin again" in Miami

description: Paul Whelan reflects on how WNBA star Brittney Griner helped lend support and advocated for his freedom after he was left behind in a one-for-one prisoner swap between the U.S. and Russia in December 2022. Griner returned home after spending nearly 10 months in Russian custody for drug charges
title: Paul Whelan says Brittney Griner was "a great help" in advocating for his freedom from Russia

description: President Biden has arrived in Berlin for talks with global allies as he pushes for continued support of Ukraine in their war against Russia. CBS News White House reporter Willie James Inman has more.

description: Late Thursday night, the Texas Supreme Court issued a last-minute stay of execution for Robert Roberson, who was set to become the first person in the U.S. executed for a murder conviction linked to shaken baby syndrome. CBS News correspondent Nikki Battiste has more.
title: Texas Supreme Court halts execution of Robert Roberson in "shaken baby syndrome" case

description: Kamala Harris and Donald Trump were back on the campaign trail trading barbs Thursday. Harris held a rally in Wisconsin where she said Trump was clueless about women's health care, while Trump appeared at the Al Smith Dinner in New York City, bashing Harris for not being there. CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi has more.
title: Harris slams Trump for IVF comments, Trump calls Harris disrespectful for skipping Al Smith Dinner

description:
This Sunday, Jon Wertheim travels to Door County, Wisconsin, where residents have voted for the winning candidate in every presidential election this century. It’s the only swing state county with
 this distinction.

title: CVS Health CEO Karen Lynch steps down after 19% stock plunge

description: New details are coming out about the Israeli operation that killed Yahya Sinwar, Hamas' top commander in Gaza. CBS News reporter Haley Ott has the latest.
title: What we know about the operation that killed Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar

description: President Biden says he told Israel's leader to make the killing of Hamas' leader "an opportunity" for peace in Gaza.

description: Twelve jurors and four alternates were chosen Monday and Tuesday in Fort Wayne, Indiana, to hear Richard Allen's trial in the 2017 killings of 13-year-old Abigail Williams and 14-year-old Liberty German.

description: Ina Kenoyer believed Steven Riley Jr. was about to come into a large inheritance and had planned to break up with her, authorities say.
